  "reasoning": "The bug occurs when an RPC call (like getattr) is interrupted by a signal and returns -ERESTARTSYS. The nfs3_rpc_wrapper function only has special handling for -EJUKEBOX errors but doesn't properly handle -ERESTARTSYS when returned directly from rpc_call_sync. When a signal interrupts the RPC call, the wrapper breaks the loop and returns -ERESTARTSYS to the NFS code. The NFS code (__nfs_revalidate_inode) then treats this as a genuine error and invalidates the inode, causing all mounts on that inode to be unmounted. The wrapper needs to handle -ERESTARTSYS similar to how it handles -EJUKEBOX - by retrying the operation with appropriate checks for pending signals. The problematic code is in the nfs3_rpc_wrapper function at fs/nfs/nfs3proc.c, specifically the condition 'if (res != -EJUKEBOX)' which should also check for -ERESTARTSYS to implement proper retry logic for signal-interrupted RPC calls."
}

